        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 8:11AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 811 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
east of Salina, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Colcord...                        Leach...
Hoot Owl...                       Twin Oaks...
Rose...                           Kansas...
Lake Eucha State Park...          Natural Falls State Park...
Oaks...                           Salina...
West Siloam Springs...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
